53
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:10,078
-What?
-Still, I'll always be here for Sol-i.

54
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:14,499
Open this for me.

55
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:16,167
Open it.

56
00:06:18,169 --> 00:06:19,629
Great job.

57
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:21,256
Here. Take it.

58
00:06:21,339 --> 00:06:24,050
-What? Why--
-Yes, thank you.

59
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:27,721
Come on. What's wrong?

60
00:06:27,804 --> 00:06:29,681
You get on my nerves.

61
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:32,475
Did you eat?

62
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:33,685
No, not yet.

63
00:06:38,857 --> 00:06:39,858
Dr. Seo.

64
00:06:41,651 --> 00:06:44,446
-Are you busy?
-Have you been looking for me?

65
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:47,407
Who will do the surgery
on patient Shin Gi-heon, Room 1504?

66
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:50,410
So you were looking for me for a reason.

67
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:53,163
Solve this riddle if you want the answer.

68
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:55,540
Which martial arts
does Winnie the Pooh practice?

69
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:59,461
-Kung "Pooh."
-What? That was fast.

70
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:01,004
Who will perform the surgery?

71
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:04,090
Dr. Kim Hyeon-gi will,
and I'll be assisting him.

72
00:07:04,174 --> 00:07:05,550
Why are you asking?

73
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:07,969
Please do your best.

74
00:07:08,053 --> 00:07:11,431
What? That's unlike you
to ask for a favor.

75
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:12,849
Is that all?

76
00:07:12,932 --> 00:07:13,850
Bye.

77
00:07:15,644 --> 00:07:16,728
What's it about?

78
00:07:17,729 --> 00:07:18,563
Damn it.

79
00:07:18,647 --> 00:07:21,358
Why didn't Sol-i tell us the room number?

80
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:22,442
I know, right?

81
00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:24,235
She's not answering her phone either.

82
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:26,905
-Which room is it?
-Thank you.

83
00:07:28,031 --> 00:07:28,907
Where is she?

84
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:31,493
Jin-hwan.

85
00:07:35,497 --> 00:07:37,082
What am I looking at?

86
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:40,835
Ha-young, I think
I need to be hospitalized again.

87
00:07:40,919 --> 00:07:42,253
I'm seeing things.

88
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:43,713
Cha Heon is in front of me.

89
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:44,839
Your eyes are fine.

90
00:07:44,923 --> 00:07:46,216
It's been a while.

91
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,801
It's you.

92
00:07:49,094 --> 00:07:50,679
It really is you, Heon.

93
00:07:50,762 --> 00:07:53,974
What? Weren't you going to settle
in the States?

94
00:07:54,057 --> 00:07:56,518
Right. Why didn't you even give us a call?

95
00:07:57,936 --> 00:07:58,812
Sorry.

96
00:08:02,273 --> 00:08:04,359
It's good to see you again.

97
00:08:04,442 --> 00:08:05,694
I'm glad you're back.

98
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:08,405
I missed you, my friend.

99
00:08:22,794 --> 00:08:24,713
Get in. I'll drive you home.

100
